- --------------
- --- Update ---
- --------------

SGI has released Patch 10098 - SGI ProPack v2.4: SGI Advanced Linux
Environment security update #24 which includes updated SGI ProPack v2.4
RPMs for the SGI Altix family of systems, in response to the
following security issues:

Updated Ethereal packages fix security issues
 http://rhn.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2004-378.html

GNOME VFS updates address extfs vulnerability
 http://rhn.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2004-373.html

Updated glibc packages fix flaws
 http://rhn.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2004-383.html

Updated libpng packages fix security issues
 http://rhn.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2004-402.html

Updated mozilla packages fix security issues
 http://rhn.redhat.com/errata/RHSA-2004-421.html


Patch 10098 is available from http://support.sgi.com/ and
ftp://patches.sgi.com/support/free/security/patches/ProPack/2.4/

The individual RPMs from Patch 10098 are available from:
ftp://oss.sgi.com/projects/sgi_propack/download/2.4/updates/RPMS
ftp://oss.sgi.com/projects/sgi_propack/download/2.4/updates/SRPMS


